## Step 1: Multiply the first equation by $zw$ and the second equation by $z^2w^2$
This gives us two equations, \begin{align*}
zw(z + \frac{20i}w) &= (5+i)zw, \\
z^2w^2(z + \frac{20i}w) &= z^2w^2(-4+10i).
\end{align*}

## Step 2: Simplify the first equation, combining like terms
\begin{align*}
z^2w -20iz &= 5wz + 5iwz \Longrightarrow z^2w-5wz-5iwz-20iz=0.
\end{align*}

## Step 3: Simplify the new term in the equation, combining $i$ terms
\begin{align*}
z^2w-5wz-5iwz-20iz &\Longrightarrow z^2w-5wz+i(-5wz-20z)+20iz \\ 
& \Longrightarrow z^2w-5iwz-5wz-20iz+20iz \\ 
& \Longrightarrow z^2w-5iwz-5wz.
\end{align*}


## Step 4: Factor $w$ from the equation
$w(z^2-5z-5iz) =0$

## Step 5: Multiply the second equation by $zw$ and simplify the new equation, combining like terms
\begin{align*}
zw(z^2w^2(z + \frac{20i}w)) &= zw*z^2w^2(-4+10i) \\
z^3w^3(z + \frac{20i}w) &= z^3w^3(-4+10i) \\
z^4w^4 - 20iz^3w^3 &=  - 4 zw^4 + 10izw^4.
\end{align*}

## Step 6: Factor out the $zw^4 $ term
\begin{align*}
z^4w^4 -20iw^3zw^3 - 4 zw^4 + 10iw^3zw^3 &= 0\\
z^4w^4-4z^3w^4+(-20+10)i^2z^2w^3+10z^3w^4-20z^3w^3+20iw^3z^3-10z^3w^4&=0.
\\ zw^4(z^3-4w^3)+(-20+10)iw^3(zw)+10z^3w^4-10z^2w^4*&=0
\\zw^4 (z^3-4w^3)+6iw^3 zw + z^2 w^4(z-10)&=0
\end{align*}

## Step 7: Now we have a system with two apparent equations and two variables:
\begin{align*}
z^2w(z + \frac{20i}w)&=5i(wz)\\
z^2w(z + \frac{20i}w)-z^2iw &=5i(zw)-5iw^2\\
z^2w^2(z+20/wi)=5&im(zw)- 5i w^2.
\end{align*}

## Step 8: Note the error in the previous steps.
Let us simply take the first equation in Step 2, $z^2w-5wz-5iwz-20iz = 0$, and examine it again to see what we can deduce about our complex numbers $z$ and $w$. Then rationalize the equation which then takes the form of

\[wz^2-\frac{125}{i}z^2-i^2 5 i w
z-\frac{20}{i} iz =0 \].

## Step 9: Determine that the previous rationalization introduced a sign error.
And at this point we should think let us multiply each of the form terms that appear by 5/5 this will allow us to work more cleanly with our rationalized version: \begin{align*} 
\frac{5}{i} (i wz^2) - 125zi^2w - \frac{5}{i}} (5z^2) + 100izi. 
\end{align*}

